WEBVTT

00:09.651 --> 00:11.818
[Thunder]

00:13.000 --> 00:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:28.402 --> 00:29.537
[Sighs]

00:29.703 --> 00:31.104
[Snap]

00:36.110 --> 00:37.386
Anybody there?

00:37.511 --> 00:38.546
[Wings flap]

00:38.712 --> 00:40.513
[Horse neighs]

00:43.842 --> 00:45.428
Drop the rifle.

00:45.594 --> 00:48.520
Turn around.

00:50.932 --> 00:52.894
You Harper?

00:53.126 --> 00:54.312
No, sir.

00:56.629 --> 00:58.065
Where is he?

01:00.298 --> 01:01.694
Who wants to know?

01:03.135 --> 01:04.878
I'm your new foreman.

01:05.003 --> 01:06.946
Why should I believe you?

01:07.071 --> 01:08.915
Well, I guess Mr. Durant
didn't have time

01:09.040 --> 01:10.850
to come out and tell you his self.

01:10.975 --> 01:12.319
Durant?

01:12.444 --> 01:13.720
Yeah, he told me to come
look for Harper.

01:13.845 --> 01:15.221
Why?

01:15.346 --> 01:17.723
That's his business.

01:17.848 --> 01:19.337
Where is he?

01:19.503 --> 01:22.548
[Sighs]
Harper hightailed it.

01:22.714 --> 01:23.862
When?

01:23.987 --> 01:25.468
- A few hours ago.
- Which way?

01:25.634 --> 01:27.595
North.

01:27.761 --> 01:30.264
Towards the Ridge.

01:30.493 --> 01:32.099
Is it true about Johnson?

01:32.265 --> 01:33.935
Yeah, it's true.

01:34.101 --> 01:36.604
What's the world comin' to, sir?

01:36.770 --> 01:40.111
The world ain't
comin' to nothin', son.

01:40.236 --> 01:42.443
Same as it ever was.

01:42.672 --> 01:44.528
[Horse neighs]

02:10.220 --> 02:11.555
Harper!

02:13.067 --> 02:15.144
Harper!

02:15.269 --> 02:16.869
Is that you?

02:23.343 --> 02:24.743
[Gunshot]

02:31.074 --> 02:32.159
[Gunshot]

02:44.838 --> 02:47.049
[Gunshot]

02:47.215 --> 02:48.509
[Gunshot]

02:50.135 --> 02:51.244
[Gunshot]

02:51.369 --> 02:52.763
[Horse neighs]
Whoa.

03:01.146 --> 03:02.773
[Horse whining]

03:08.111 --> 03:09.027
Uhh!

03:09.152 --> 03:10.698
Shit!

03:13.033 --> 03:15.119
[Horse whinnying]

03:24.467 --> 03:25.629
Shh shh shh.

03:25.795 --> 03:27.673
Shh shh shh.

03:32.475 --> 03:34.180
Shh shh.

03:40.783 --> 03:42.750
[Gunshot]

04:13.093 --> 04:16.387
<font color="#3399FF">Sync and correction by Mlmlte</font>
<font color="#3399FF">www.addic7ed.com</font>

04:41.207 --> 04:43.450
Mrs. Bell?

04:43.575 --> 04:47.721
Mrs. Bell, it's me, Thomas Durant.

04:47.846 --> 04:51.173
They said you were up here.

04:51.339 --> 04:55.886
I know who you are...
Mr. Durant.

04:58.256 --> 04:59.932
The whole world's been looking

05:00.057 --> 05:03.561
for you and, uh...
Here you are.

05:05.326 --> 05:07.314
And here I am.

05:15.372 --> 05:16.448
Uh.

05:22.358 --> 05:24.915
You must excuse my appearance.

05:25.081 --> 05:29.394
We need to get you
some medical attention.

05:29.519 --> 05:32.214
Please... allow me to escort you.

05:34.341 --> 05:41.599
Ah, you... you won't
need this anymore.

05:43.558 --> 05:46.478
Your ordeal is over.

06:03.483 --> 06:07.663
My deepest condolences
on your loss, Mrs. Bell.

06:07.788 --> 06:08.918
Thank you.

06:10.424 --> 06:12.000
How in God's name

06:12.125 --> 06:14.536
did you make your way back here?

06:14.661 --> 06:19.807
Uh... can't remember his name, um...

06:19.932 --> 06:23.010
A Southerner, I think.

06:23.135 --> 06:24.378
Bohannon?

06:24.503 --> 06:28.306
Yes, I believe so.

06:29.942 --> 06:31.774
Hmm.

06:31.940 --> 06:33.387
[Train whistle blowing]

06:33.512 --> 06:35.313
[Laughter and chatter]

06:45.286 --> 06:47.133
Did I tell ya about me rendez-vous

06:47.258 --> 06:48.665
with the tattooed harlot?

06:51.162 --> 06:53.339
The Scarlet whore of Babylon

06:53.464 --> 06:55.641
had nothing on this lass, I tell ya.

06:55.766 --> 06:57.299
Man:
Give us the particulars, man.

06:57.465 --> 07:01.213
I have never seen nothin' like
it in all me life, boys.

07:01.338 --> 07:05.683
She used her organ like a velvet
hand on me tally whacker.

07:05.943 --> 07:07.852
[Chuckles]
And to hear her tell it,

07:07.977 --> 07:10.221
she's practiced these
dark arts of love

07:10.346 --> 07:12.022
on all manner of beasts and men.

07:12.281 --> 07:15.526
Chinks and monkeys and horses

07:15.692 --> 07:18.654
have all known
the pleasure of her touch.

07:18.820 --> 07:21.232
In fact, there is but one creature

07:21.357 --> 07:23.909
in all the world with whom
she refuses to copulate.

07:24.125 --> 07:25.425
And what would that be?

07:25.702 --> 07:27.079
Well, the common American
nigger of course.

07:27.295 --> 07:28.330
Damn it, I've heard enough...

07:28.563 --> 07:29.790
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

07:34.711 --> 07:36.422
[Chuckles]

07:36.588 --> 07:39.172
All right.

07:46.597 --> 07:49.558
Never thought I'd see you again.

07:49.683 --> 07:51.384
You kill him?

07:53.387 --> 07:55.897
Where you going?

07:56.022 --> 07:59.528
Sooner or later,
you gotta give us some orders, boss man.

08:00.760 --> 08:03.237
The demise of head
surveyor Robert Bell

08:03.362 --> 08:05.707
and party, a great loss to railroad.

08:05.832 --> 08:07.108
Stop.

08:07.233 --> 08:10.545
Bell's work must continue.
Stop.

08:10.670 --> 08:13.814
Send funds for new surveyors at once.

08:13.939 --> 08:15.252
Stop.

08:15.418 --> 08:16.962
[Knock on door]

08:20.423 --> 08:22.343
What news?

08:22.509 --> 08:28.428
Payroll is late... work
disorganized and slow.

08:28.553 --> 08:31.997
This new foreman of yours
just up and leave yesterday.

08:32.121 --> 08:33.645
Nobody seen him since.

08:33.811 --> 08:36.732
He rode out to rendez-vous
with the tree cutting party.

08:36.898 --> 08:41.779
He informed me yesterday
at our morning briefing.

08:41.945 --> 08:44.008
There's something about this man.

08:44.133 --> 08:45.991
He's up to something.

08:46.157 --> 08:48.413
He crossed paths with Mrs. Bell.

08:48.538 --> 08:49.648
Bohannon?

08:49.773 --> 08:51.038
He brought her in.

08:51.204 --> 08:52.247
Did she have the maps?

08:52.475 --> 08:53.551
Shh.

08:53.676 --> 08:55.250
She's right next door.

08:57.846 --> 09:01.425
[Sighs]
No, she didn't have them.

09:01.550 --> 09:05.135
How will you reach the
Pacific without them?

09:05.301 --> 09:06.637
You let me worry about that.

09:08.390 --> 09:12.726
Oh, there's a supply train
arriving tomorrow morning

09:12.892 --> 09:15.437
with a shipment of black powder.

09:15.603 --> 09:20.442
My men will meet the train
and guard it all morning.

09:25.105 --> 09:28.409
New telegram to my damn stock broker.

09:28.575 --> 09:36.224
Invest $147,000 in R&R
railroad stock as discussed.

09:36.349 --> 09:37.835
Stop.

09:48.127 --> 09:49.804
Ahem.

09:49.929 --> 09:51.098
Mrs. Bell?

09:56.868 --> 09:58.814
Are you all right in there?

10:00.438 --> 10:03.817
Yes, thank you, Mr. Durant.

10:03.942 --> 10:07.120
I, uh, ahem, I brought out my...

10:07.245 --> 10:10.824
Personal Chef from Delmonico's
in New York City.

10:10.949 --> 10:15.761
I wondered if you would like to
join me for dinner this evening?

10:15.886 --> 10:18.522
Yes, that would be wonderful.

10:23.961 --> 10:26.467
Is there anything else
I can get for you?

10:30.167 --> 10:35.047
Actually, has the reward
been given to anyone?

10:35.172 --> 10:37.978
Uh, I believe it
belongs to Mr. Bohannon.

10:38.144 --> 10:39.851
I don't think he's claimed it.

10:39.976 --> 10:41.440
Would you like me
to see that he gets it?

10:41.606 --> 10:43.355
No.

10:43.480 --> 10:46.361
There's someone else who deserves it.

10:47.983 --> 10:49.384
[Cow mooing]

10:51.387 --> 10:53.555
[Train whistle blowing]

10:57.580 --> 10:59.458
[Music playing]

11:10.271 --> 11:12.105
[Man whistles]

11:18.778 --> 11:20.622
Stay off my corner, sweetheart,

11:20.747 --> 11:23.316
unless she wants her
own crib, right, ladies?

11:23.940 --> 11:25.859
[Laughter]

11:26.025 --> 11:27.069
Leave her alone.

11:27.235 --> 11:28.464
What do you say, blondie?

11:28.589 --> 11:30.499
Them Injuns teach you anything?

11:30.624 --> 11:32.501
[Hollering]
Leave her alone!

11:32.626 --> 11:34.535
Hey, I'm sorry, ma'am.

11:34.701 --> 11:37.454
These dirty whores don't know
a lady when they see one.

11:41.916 --> 11:45.012
Where there is hatred,
let me show love.

11:45.137 --> 11:48.316
Where there is injury, pardon.

11:48.441 --> 11:51.260
Where there is doubt, faith.

11:51.426 --> 11:53.186
Amen.

11:53.311 --> 11:55.212
Joseph?

11:56.448 --> 11:58.782
Mrs. Bell?

12:01.553 --> 12:03.897
You look like you're
feeling much better.

12:04.063 --> 12:06.441
It's amazing what
a little soap and water can do.

12:07.991 --> 12:09.987
I didn't mean to leave that night.

12:10.153 --> 12:11.437
But that man...

12:11.562 --> 12:13.323
There's no need to explain.

12:14.565 --> 12:16.159
You've cut your hair.

12:16.325 --> 12:17.776
Yes, ma'am.

12:17.901 --> 12:18.996
Did you come to pray?

12:19.162 --> 12:22.614
No, um... I came to give you this.

12:22.739 --> 12:25.082
It's the reward money.
No, please, take it.

12:25.207 --> 12:26.628
I can't.

12:26.794 --> 12:29.061
There'll be no trouble,
nobody knows it was you.

12:29.380 --> 12:31.322
No, that's not it.

12:31.447 --> 12:33.844
I'm not a bounty hunter.

12:34.010 --> 12:35.726
It's my duty to help.

12:35.851 --> 12:38.962
Joseph, that money will
buy a lot of bibles.

12:39.087 --> 12:41.852
Mrs. Bell, Reverend Cole.

12:42.018 --> 12:43.924
Reverend.

12:44.395 --> 12:46.077
Your donations are always welcome.

12:47.023 --> 12:48.692
Please.

12:48.858 --> 12:50.777
Thank you.

12:50.943 --> 12:52.821
So, this is the fair-haired
maiden of the West?

12:52.987 --> 12:54.573
I beg your pardon?

13:04.165 --> 13:07.122
"Robert Bell fought valiantly to save

13:07.247 --> 13:08.462
the virtue of his beautiful wife,

13:08.628 --> 13:12.685
killing a savage
with his final breath.

13:14.887 --> 13:16.637
Is that not how it happened?

13:16.803 --> 13:19.000
Yes.

13:19.125 --> 13:23.101
My husband... saved my life.

13:23.267 --> 13:26.021
Well... what about
the rest of it? Um...

13:27.480 --> 13:28.940
Outnumbered 10 to one?

13:29.106 --> 13:30.817
Sullied by the savages?

13:30.983 --> 13:32.527
I didn't write it.

13:32.693 --> 13:34.029
But this is true?

13:34.195 --> 13:35.405
Of course not.

13:35.571 --> 13:37.824
Well, Indians will die
as a result of this.

13:37.990 --> 13:39.687
The Indians attacked us.

13:39.812 --> 13:42.454
If they die, they will
be to blame, not me.

13:42.620 --> 13:43.622
Maybe you've heard of
the Sand Creek massacre?

13:43.788 --> 13:45.248
I didn't come here to speak of this.

13:45.414 --> 13:47.728
You know, the Cheyenne were
flying the American flag

13:47.853 --> 13:49.562
over their camp and it
didn't stop the U.S. Calvary

13:49.687 --> 13:52.255
from killing 100 innocent
women and children.

13:52.421 --> 13:53.366
That was a terrible
thing that happened.

13:53.491 --> 13:54.841
I wasn't a part of it.

13:55.007 --> 13:56.203
Please, I'm just saying,

13:56.328 --> 13:57.552
try to see the bigger picture.

13:57.718 --> 13:59.805
My husband was slaughtered
right in front of me.

13:59.930 --> 14:04.017
It's a little difficult
to see the bigger picture.

14:04.183 --> 14:05.869
Good day.

14:34.129 --> 14:35.139
[Harmonica playing]

14:35.264 --> 14:37.098
Hey.

14:38.767 --> 14:40.577
Hey, hey.

14:40.702 --> 14:44.138
That son of a bitch
got away because of you.

14:45.607 --> 14:47.216
Because of me?
How you figure that?

14:47.341 --> 14:50.063
You killed Johnson before
he could give me Harper's name.

14:52.148 --> 14:53.355
Oh.

14:53.480 --> 14:56.987
Well, I... I killed Johnson
before he killed you.

14:57.153 --> 14:58.594
Now...

14:58.719 --> 15:00.365
But I would have got
a name out of him.

15:00.531 --> 15:01.908
He would have blowed your brains out.

15:02.074 --> 15:03.165
And then I could have killed Harper

15:03.290 --> 15:04.703
before he had a chance to run.

15:04.869 --> 15:07.260
You're either drunk or crazy or both.

15:11.231 --> 15:13.628
You have any idea
what they took from me?

15:15.568 --> 15:18.967
They ain't took nothin' from you
that ain't been took from me.

15:25.640 --> 15:28.029
{pub}Fly away home, just a nickel a show.

15:29.518 --> 15:31.976
Feel the mist against your cheeks.

15:33.189 --> 15:34.649
Give it a rest, Mick.

15:34.815 --> 15:40.228
They're sick and bloody tired
of the mighty Shannon

15:40.353 --> 15:44.951
and the blarney stone...
The bloody Irish bog.

15:45.117 --> 15:47.701
Well, then we need new slides.

15:47.826 --> 15:49.706
New slides cost money.

15:49.872 --> 15:51.500
You've got some copper
squirreled away, brother,

15:51.666 --> 15:52.667
now's the time to tell me.

15:52.833 --> 15:54.586
Maybe we should relocate.

15:54.752 --> 15:57.130
The rent is low down by
the slaughterhouse, right?

15:57.296 --> 15:58.378
The rent was low
in Wicklow, too, Mick.

16:00.883 --> 16:02.605
We're done with that shit.

16:03.940 --> 16:06.181
It was a high rent dream
that brought us out here.

16:06.347 --> 16:10.435
I'm not going to let that big
Swedish bastard kill our dream.

16:10.601 --> 16:12.224
Am I right?

16:12.349 --> 16:14.773
Mick?

16:14.939 --> 16:17.067
Hold on now.

16:17.233 --> 16:19.653
I just had a grand idea.

16:19.819 --> 16:21.571
Oh, no.

16:21.737 --> 16:23.324
It's a business idea.

16:24.794 --> 16:27.104
Ideas ain't your strong suit, Mick.

16:27.229 --> 16:28.620
Ah, ha ha.

16:28.786 --> 16:29.940
This one's golden.

16:30.065 --> 16:31.540
I'll prove it to ya.

16:33.541 --> 16:37.921
I've taken the liberty of
telegraphing your family in England.

16:38.087 --> 16:40.850
I just wanted them
to know you were well.

16:40.975 --> 16:42.753
Thank you, Mr. Durant.

16:42.878 --> 16:46.012
I'm afraid you'll grow
weary of my gratitude.

16:46.178 --> 16:49.683
I don't know what news of
the attack may have reached them.

16:49.849 --> 16:53.854
I didn't want your father
worrying needlessly.

16:54.020 --> 16:56.265
I'm sure my father was happy to hear

16:56.390 --> 16:59.067
he was right...

16:59.233 --> 17:00.861
About me coming to America.

17:01.027 --> 17:02.696
He was against it, no doubt?

17:02.862 --> 17:06.207
My father had every aspect
of my life planned out,

17:06.332 --> 17:07.951
including whom I should marry.

17:09.952 --> 17:12.237
Robert interrupted those plans.

17:16.275 --> 17:18.086
I saw him give a lecture

17:18.252 --> 17:21.381
at the British Museum
of Natural History.

17:21.547 --> 17:24.682
He spoke of the American West.

17:29.922 --> 17:32.966
I fell in love...

17:33.091 --> 17:36.646
With him and with this land.

17:36.812 --> 17:40.606
I, too, came under Robert's spell.

17:40.731 --> 17:45.545
His dream of a transcontinental
railroad became my own.

17:45.670 --> 17:49.806
Then it's a shame you two had
such a terrible falling out.

17:50.076 --> 17:54.080
Well, Robert and I didn't
see eye to eye on everything.

17:54.246 --> 17:58.418
Such as how to squeeze every
last dollar out of the railroad.

18:01.117 --> 18:06.217
Mrs. Bell, your husband
was a starry-eyed dreamer.

18:06.383 --> 18:08.595
I am a realist.

18:08.761 --> 18:11.635
Without me, his dream would
have remained just that.

18:11.760 --> 18:14.225
Thank you for your hospitality,
Mr. Durant.

18:15.698 --> 18:17.532
Mrs. Bell, please, I'm sorry.

18:17.812 --> 18:20.273
I didn't mean to impugn Robert.

18:20.439 --> 18:23.946
Yes, he needed me,
but I needed him also.

18:24.071 --> 18:27.989
Our marriage wasn't
perfect, but it worked.

18:30.157 --> 18:33.222
Mrs. Bell, there's nowhere
for you to go out there.

18:33.347 --> 18:36.665
Please... accept my apology.

18:38.152 --> 18:41.153
Do me the honor
of remaining my guest.

18:58.769 --> 19:00.839
[Indistinct chatter]

19:29.399 --> 19:30.844
Why you following me?

19:31.010 --> 19:32.512
You tryin' to get me killed?

19:32.678 --> 19:34.480
Mister, you do that all by yourself

19:34.605 --> 19:36.516
bustin' in on a white cathouse.

19:36.682 --> 19:37.809
What you want then?

19:37.975 --> 19:39.341
Huh?

19:40.644 --> 19:42.355
You still want to give me a roll?

19:44.146 --> 19:46.776
I thought you were mighty clear
on where you stood on that.

19:46.942 --> 19:50.728
Honey, I'm already a cut rate whore
on account of my beauty marks.

19:50.853 --> 19:55.869
My white customers know I laid
with a colored fella, I starve.

19:56.035 --> 20:01.305
But... if you got a dollar,

20:01.430 --> 20:05.336
then... maybe we can do
one off the books.

20:05.502 --> 20:08.715
Now you tryin' to get us both killed.

20:08.881 --> 20:10.605
[Chatter]

20:32.821 --> 20:35.037
[Bolan laughs]

20:35.162 --> 20:36.367
Look at him.

20:47.274 --> 20:49.917
Drop your hanky...

20:50.042 --> 20:52.050
Madam?

20:56.048 --> 20:57.449
Ah!

21:05.923 --> 21:09.136
Now, now, boys.

21:09.261 --> 21:12.605
I doubt Mr. Durant

21:12.730 --> 21:15.808
wants his new foreman assassinated.

21:15.933 --> 21:17.844
He shot my dang ear off, Swede.

21:17.969 --> 21:19.836
Too bad it was not your tongue.

21:21.505 --> 21:23.072
Move aside.

21:23.497 --> 21:28.954
Mr. Bolan, you need
to leave here right now.

21:30.690 --> 21:32.114
Damn it.

21:34.084 --> 21:38.196
Come on, Tommy, let's go.

21:38.321 --> 21:39.931
[Laughing]

21:40.056 --> 21:42.934
Let's go. Come on.

21:46.529 --> 21:49.207
Magnolias.

21:49.332 --> 21:52.944
They grow just outside
the gates of the Andersonville.

21:53.435 --> 21:59.507
Some nights, their perfume was almost
enough to mask the awful stench.

22:05.247 --> 22:09.092
Oh, you're a difficult man
to cipher, Mr. Bohannon.

22:09.217 --> 22:14.048
Let me buy you a drink.

22:14.214 --> 22:16.232
I won't turn down free liquor.

22:16.357 --> 22:17.866
Need another glass.

22:17.991 --> 22:19.168
Thank you.

22:19.293 --> 22:20.793
No.

22:24.731 --> 22:29.647
I know you killed Johnson.

22:31.371 --> 22:34.082
Hmm.

22:34.207 --> 22:38.781
What I do not know yet is why.

22:41.825 --> 22:44.091
Who are you?

22:44.216 --> 22:46.623
Hmm?

22:49.958 --> 22:52.957
Ah, I'll figure it out.

22:53.379 --> 22:54.923
You let me know when
you do, all right?

22:55.089 --> 22:57.842
[Laughing]

22:58.008 --> 23:02.108
Oh, by golly, you will be
the first to know, hmm?

23:02.233 --> 23:04.401
[Laughing]

23:06.871 --> 23:09.437
Oh, but in the meantime,

23:09.603 --> 23:13.650
I've got a business
proposition for you.

23:16.819 --> 23:21.493
Now, there is a... there
is some black powder coming in

23:21.618 --> 23:25.078
on the train...
Tomorrow morning.

23:25.244 --> 23:27.830
That is your cut.

23:27.996 --> 23:33.737
And you just look the other
way while my boys unload,

23:33.862 --> 23:38.007
uh, you know, a few barrels.

23:38.173 --> 23:43.481
Is that some of that... immoral
